public interface DmcContainerIF

The DmcContainerIF interface is implemented by objects that wrap DmcObjects and use them to store their transportable data.

updateObjectSet

void updateObjectSet(java.lang.String an,
                     java.lang.Object existing,
                     java.lang.Object newvalue)
This method is called by implementing classes once they have instantiated the appropriate value holder for an attribute value to be set on an object. By funneling all set requests through this method, we can handle things like attribute change notifications through a common mechanism.

Parameters:
an - The name of the attribute affected.
existing - The existing value, or null if there wasn't one.
newvalue - The new value for the single-valued attribute.
